For forty days Flamininus had been vainly endeavouring to find a path across the Pindus range to attack Philip, the King of Macedon, when he met a shepherd who offered to be his guide. The victory of Cynoscephalae followed, 197 Β. C. These verses are spoken by the shepherd to Flamininus.
